nces as a reviewer of the scientific programs and performance assessments of the geological repository for transuranic waste at the waste isolation pilot plant in new mexico and the proposed repository for spent nuclear fuel and high level waste at yucca mountain in nevada he has served on numerous committees of the national research council that have addressed many aspects of nuclear waste management ewing identifies multiple recommendations for the blue ribbon commission on america's nuclear future and details each one such as licensing of geologic repositories site selection and risk management downloads pdf+ standards & regulations for the geologic disposal of spent nuclear fuel and high level waste by rodney ewing modified august 2011 pdf ewing_brc_white_paper_final pd pdf 806.4 kb pdf+ go to site external http brc gov sites default files parent events standards and regulations for deep geological disposal of radioactive waste june 6 2011 workshop edward blandford rodney c ewing bob budnitz pdf+ 3 papers 2 conference agendas available parent research health and the environment nuclear security and risk topics nuclear energy mexico united states search cisac publications everything publications of interest international regime of fresh fuel supply and spent fuel disposal chaim braun michael m may nonproliferation review vol 13 1 2006 pdf+ cover spent nuclear fuel jordi bruno rodney c ewing elements vol 2 2006 pdf+ the key role of the back end in the nuclear fuel cycle thomas isaacs charles mccombie daedalus vol vol 2 2010 pdf+ cover raising global physical protection standards for weapon usable nuclear material george bunn institute of nuclear materials management 41st annual meeting 2000 support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 9625 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
